Thursday Nov. 11 1926
My Dear Katherine,

    I have been going to write for over a week but it seems like today and it is now 4:55 P.M.
    I had a talk with the doctor at Lombard election P.M. and he said unless I took his treatment two years was as long as I had ahead of me. Well I didn't like the report but am of the opinion with propper care and eats the m.d. night have been mistaken. I am using the morning exercises as put out by the Victor Phonograph Co. and tho used only three times as have had the records only three days, seem to have even at this early date has helped so it seems anyway I am in hopes that the exercises will be helpful.
    I wanted to ask you while at Glen Ellyn more about eats. I am off the whole wheat for breakfast and eat two soft boiled eggs, 4 slices of whole wheat bread, tosted and a pint of milk. At noon a can of the soup as you fixed it, and the ballance of a pint of
